verbose_text: The evidence that VPS34-IN1 suppresses Vps34 activity in vivo is supported by the observation that treatment of cells with VPS34-IN1 induces a strikingly rapid dose dependent dispersal of the localization of the PtdIns (3) P binding GFP-2xFYVE Hrs from endosomal membranes (XREF_FIG, XREF_FIG and XREF_FIG), where PtdIns (3) P is produced by Vps34 resides [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
